						<summary>

						<p>Pedestal in an enclosure near the Pātālēśvara shrine in the Kumārasvāmin temple on the Kumārasvāmi hill.</p>						

						<p>1042 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 9[6]7, Pārthiva Vaiśākha śu. 6, Thursday</hi> corresponding <hi rend="bold">1042 A.D., April 25.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the installation of (an image of) a peacock by the goldsmith <hi rend="italic">(akkasāle)</hi> Chandāchāri, son off Hampāchāri of Orvvay. It refers to Bayna-kula. </p>						

						</summary>
